    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect minimum length check in KSI and Sequence Number encoding\n\n### Summary\nThe KSI and Sequence Number IE encoding function was using an incorrect minimum length check that caused valid encodings to be rejected. When IEI=0, only 1 byte is needed, but the check required 2 bytes, leading to downstream issues.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/IES/KsiAndSequenceNumber.h`: Changed `KSI_AND_SEQUENCE_NUMBER_MINIMUM_LENGTH` from 2 to 1\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen encoding a Service Request message with IEI=0 for the KSI and Sequence Number field, the encoding would fail with a buffer too short error even though only 1 byte was actually needed. This caused message encoding to fail in valid scenarios where the buffer was exactly 1 byte long for this field.\n\nThe issue manifested as failed NAS message encodings in scenarios where the KSI and Sequence Number IE was included without an IEI tag, which is common in mandatory fields.\n"
}